<section>
  <h2>Mechanism & Disease Links</h2>
  <img src="assets/aif1-diagram.png" alt="AIF1 mechanism diagram">
  <p>AIF1 binds actin to regulate macrophage cytoskeleton, contributing to inflammation and tissue repair. Overexpression is linked to chronic inflammation and graft rejection.</p>
  <p>Potential drug action: blocking AIF1-actin interaction could dampen macrophage activation.</p>
</section>
